org.xflatdb.xflat.db

Enum EngineState

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<EngineState>
      • org.xflatdb.xflat.db.EngineState
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<EngineState>

    public enum EngineState
extends java.lang.Enum<EngineState>
    Represents the progression of states in an engine as it is used.

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      Running
      The state of an engine that has a write lock and sole access to the underlying data store.
      SpinningDown
      The state of an engine that is in the process of shutting down.
      SpinningUp
      The state of an engine that is in the process of initializing.
      SpunDown
      The state of an engine that has finished shutting down and is no longer expecting even read operations.
      SpunUp
      The state of an engine that has finished initializing and is waiting to be notified that it can have sole access to the underlying data.
      Uninitialized
      The state of a newly instantiated engine, before it is ready.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • Uninitialized

        public static final EngineState Uninitialized
        The state of a newly instantiated engine, before it is ready. Any operations on this engine will throw.

      • SpinningUp

        public static final EngineState SpinningUp
        The state of an engine that is in the process of initializing. At this point the engine can obtain a read-lock on the underlying data.

      • SpunUp

        public static final EngineState SpunUp
        The state of an engine that has finished initializing and is waiting to be notified that it can have sole access to the underlying data.

      • Running

        public static final EngineState Running
        The state of an engine that has a write lock and sole access to the underlying data store.

      • SpinningDown

        public static final EngineState SpinningDown
        The state of an engine that is in the process of shutting down. At this point the engine releases its write lock and only responds to read requests from outstanding cursors.

      • SpunDown

        public static final EngineState SpunDown
        The state of an engine that has finished shutting down and is no longer expecting even read operations. Any operations on this engine will throw.
